
Key features of Loom :

Screen Recording: Capture your computer screen, webcam, and microphone simultaneously.
Instant Sharing: Share video links instantly with others.
Video Editing: Trim and edit your videos easily.
Call-to-Action Buttons: Add interactive buttons to your videos.
Password Protection: Protect your videos with passwords.
Integrations: Works with tools like Slack, Gmail, and GitHub.
Folders and Organization: Organize your videos into folders.
Viewer Insights: See who watched your video and for how long.
Drawing Tools: Annotate your screen while recording.
Custom Thumbnails: Choose a specific thumbnail for your video.
Comments and Reactions: Allow viewers to leave comments and reactions on your videos.
Team Library: Share and manage videos within your team.
Transcription: Automatic transcription of your videoâ€™s audio.
Analytics: Detailed analytics on video performance.
Embed Options: Embed videos on websites and blogs.
Mobile App: Record and share videos from your mobile device.




flow:

1. Getting Started
  Sign Up: Create an account using your email, Google, or Slack.
  Install Loom: Use the desktop app (Windows or macOS), Chrome extension, or mobile app (iOS and Android).


2. Recording a Video
  Open Loom: Launch the app or extension.
  Choose Recording Mode:
    Screen and Camera: Record your screen and yourself.
    Screen Only: Record just your screen.
    Camera Only: Record only yourself.
  Set-Up:
    Microphone: Select your audio source.
    Camera: Choose your webcam if recording yourself.
    Quality: Adjust video quality settings.
  Start Recording: Click "Start Recording" and begin. You can use tools to draw, highlight, or pause during recording.

3. Editing the Video
  Basic Edits:
    Trim: Cut out the start or end of the video.
    Cut: Remove parts from the middle.
    Stitch: Combine multiple clips.
    Text: Add text annotations.
  Advanced Edits:
    Call-to-Action: Add a clickable button.
    Thumbnail: Choose or upload a video thumbnail.
    Privacy: Set your video to public, private, or link-only.

4. Sharing the Video
  Share Options:
    Link: Copy and share the video link.
    Embed: Get a code to embed the video on websites.
    Direct Share: Post directly to Slack, Twitter, or Facebook.

5. Managing Videos
  Library: Organize videos in folders.
  Search: Find videos quickly with search and filters.

6. Analytics and Feedback
  View Counts: See how many times your video was watched.
  Comments: Viewers can leave comments, which you can reply to. Comments are time-stamped for specific feedback.

7. Integration
  Tools: Connect Loom with Slack, Google Workspace, Notion, and more for easy sharing.

8. Mobile App Features
  Record: Create videos from your mobile device.
  Manage and Share: Access, edit, and share videos directly from your phone.

